description:
New acquisitions of rhizobia are investigated in order to: 

 &middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; overcome poor N 2  fixation from an existing symbiotic relationship; 

 &middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; select well-adapted strains for a difficult environment ( e.g.  acid soil); 

 &middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; assist in legume domestication programs; 

 &middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; match with sequenced legumes for genetic studies of N 2  fixation undertake biodiversity studies.

